Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONSECUTIVE), with credit for 3 DAYS time served.  

AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONSECUTIVE).

AS TO COUNT 3:
The court sentenced the defendant to 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONSECUTIVE).

AS TO ALL COUNTS:
Court STAYED sentences and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time (as to COUNT 1), STAYED pending review;
-Any programming with CHIPS can be applied to probation, proof to be submitted to the agent;
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment;
-Parenting classes;
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
-Absolute sobriety;
-No contact with victims I.R., B.R., R.R., or R.R. except as authorized by DMCPS and CHIPS;
-Obtain/maintain employment;
-Cooperate with CHIPS and DMCPS;
-No corporal punishment of any kind;
-No contact with firearms;
-Provide DNA sample;
-Court WAIVES all non-mandatory court costs and fees;
-Pay all mandatory supervision fees, court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharge during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant to report to probation intake and provide DNA sample by 5/5/2022.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Filed: 
Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.

Agent to request probation review hearing with the Court, if it is needed.
